trees.annotations

Annotation Type Label


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Label
    Annotation for controlling the node analysis of a node object. By default the toString()-method is used for displaying a node. If the label-annotation is used, these methods will supply the label. Only methods with no parameters and a returning object are allowed. If more than one method is annotated, the label will be made up of all results.
    Author:
    Marcus deininger
